  <refnamediv>
    <refname>&dhpackage;</refname>

    <refpurpose>Interactively monitor status of RTS2 components.</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>
  <refsect1>
    <title>DESCRIPTION</title>

    <para>
      Rts2-mon is ncurses based program, which display status of RTS2 components. It also display
      various system logs.
    </para>

  </refsect1>
  <refsect1>
    <title>KEYS</title>
    
    <para>
      These keys control rts2-mon behaviour:
    </para>

    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>
          <option>F2</option>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <para>Switch RTS2 to off state.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>
          <option>F3</option>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <para>Switch RTS2 to standby state.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>
          <option>F4</option>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <para>Switch RTS2 to on state.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>
          <option>F5</option>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <para>Refresh display.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>
          <option>F8</option>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <para>Toggle between message and status display.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>
          <option>F9</option>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <para>Toggle between short and long status display.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>
          <option>F10</option>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <para>Exit from rts2-mon.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
    
    <title>OPTIONS</title>

    <para>
      These programs follow the usual &gnu; command line syntax,
      with long options starting with two dashes (`-').  A summary of
      options is included below.
    </para>

    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
        <term><option>-h</option>
          <option>--help</option>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <para>Show summary of options.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term><option>-V</option>
          <option>--version</option>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <para>Show version of program.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
